text: Alfonso Vázquez de Acuña (died 1474) was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as Bishop of Jaén (1457–1474) and Bishop of Mondoñedo (1455–1457)."Bishop Alfonso Vázquez de Acuña" Catholic-Hierarchy.org. David M. Cheney. Retrieved August 27, 2016"Diocese of Mondoñedo-Ferrol" Catholic-Hierarchy.org. David M. Cheney. Retrieved February 29, 2016"Diocese of Mondoñedo–Ferrol" GCatholic.org. Gabriel Chow. Retrieved February 29, 2016 ==Biography== In 1455, Alfonso Vázquez de Acuña was appointed during the papacy of Pope Callixtus III as Bishop of Mondoñedo. In 1457, he was appointed during the papacy of List of popes as Bishop of Jaén. He served as Bishop of Jaén until his death in 1474. == References == ==External links and additional sources== * (for Chronology of Bishops) * (for Chronology of Bishops) Category:15th- century Roman Catholic bishops Category:Bishops appointed by Pope Callixtus III Category:1474 deaths
